1
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,400
<i>Don't forget to clean
his navel, okay?</i>

2
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:42,067
<i> I'll do that.</i>

3
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,367
<i> Let me finish my job.</i>

4
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,500
<i>If I didn't say anything,
you wouldn't do it yourself.</i>

5
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,333
<i>Since you know better than me,
why don't you do it yourself?</i>

6
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> You're rude!</i>

7
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:51,500
<i>Did you think I would let
you get away with this?</i>

8
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> He brought that on himself.</i>

9
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:53,933
<i> He deserves it.</i>

10
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:55,533
<i> Being crippled is not easy.</i>

11
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:56,667
<i> Mom, we were crippled, too.</i>

12
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,367
<i>You lost a husband,
and we lost our father.</i>

13
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> We crawled through poverty.</i>

14
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,067
<i>Now it's his turn to crawl,
literally.</i>

15
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,567
<i> Mom, you got fired from work?</i>

16
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:04,267
<i>I need to find a job
as soon as possible.</i>

17
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,433
<i> But it will be hard for me</i>

18
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:07,633
<i>as long as I'm bound to take
care of your dad.</i>

19
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,733
<i> What do you mean?</i>

20
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:09,933
<i>I need to bring him
to the nursing home.</i>

21
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:11,533
<i> Uncle, I'm begging you.</i>

22
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:12,967
<i> Don't give up on my mom.</i>

23
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:14,567
<i>What if she wants
to give up on us?</i>

24
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,333
<i> How can I fight for someone</i>

25
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:17,433
<i>who doesn't want to fight
for our relationship?</i>

26
00:01:17,567 --> 00:01:20,533
<i>I want to know how Dad is doing.</i>

27
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:22,033
<i> Hi, Dad!</i>

28
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:24,167
<i>It's me, Coleen,
your youngest daughter.</i>

29
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:27,733
<i>You know what, Dad,
I've been longing to see you.</i>

30
00:01:27,867 --> 00:01:29,367
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

31
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,333
<i> Daddy loves you so much.</i>

32
00:01:35,267 --> 00:01:36,433
I'm waiting for a call

33
00:01:36,567 --> 00:01:38,733
from three hospitals
to which I applied.

34
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:41,633
But no one is calling me.

35
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,100
Why don't you apply at the
nursing home

36
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:46,200
where Manuel is residing?

37
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,933
Are you serious?

38
00:01:51,067 --> 00:01:53,300
I bailed on taking care
of Manuel

39
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:54,567
because it was exhausting.

40
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:57,067
And you want me to apply
for a job there?

41
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,267
But he is your husband.

42
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,833
If you come to think of it,

43
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:04,300
it is your obligation
to take care of him.

44
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,367
Easy for you to say.

45
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,167
But if you were in my position,

46
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,467
you'd understand how exhausting
it really is.

47
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,567
Like a candle
slowly burning out.

48
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:17,933
Sorry to say.

49
00:02:18,067 --> 00:02:21,633
But it could be your karma.

50
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:25,067
When you trick him
into marrying you before.

51
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:27,500
Wait a minute.

52
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:29,767
Are you my best friend?

53
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:33,167
Why are you talking
to me like that?

54
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:35,767
Instead of encouraging me
or boosting my morale

55
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:36,933
since I'm out of a job,

56
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:45,267
why are you digging up
what I did a long time ago?

57
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:49,467
I'm just being honest.

58
00:02:49,633 --> 00:02:51,967
Okay, fine, let's talk
about something else.

59
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:58,900
Actually, you can divorce
Manuel anytime now.

60
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:01,467
Since you're no longer
in Saudi Arabia,

61
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:06,767
and Manuel and Jessica believed
they're father and daughter,

62
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:08,933
nothing can convince him
otherwise.

63
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:13,267
When they're really
not related at all.

64
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:17,333
Especially now that
Manuel is a cripple.

65
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:20,700
You won't benefit
from him anymore.

66
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,500
So, if I were you...

67
00:03:25,367 --> 00:03:30,000
you deserve to have a second
chance in life.

68
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:37,200
Live life to the fullest
while you're still young.

69
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,900
Cheers.

70
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:57,400
Mom, I'm so happy that I'm able
to send Dad a video.

71
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:02,467
Jessica said Dad was moved
to tears with joy.

72
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:05,367
I can't wait to see
Dad's video message.

73
00:04:07,167 --> 00:04:10,900
Sweetie, we have to keep
this a secret, okay?

74
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:14,033
To keep our family at peace,

75
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:17,067
your siblings will get mad
if they find out.

76
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:20,167
Mom, don't worry, okay?

77
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:22,167
It's our secret.

78
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,700
I promise.

79
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,800
But mom...

80
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:35,000
Aren't you going to patch
things up with Uncle Noah?

81
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:40,067
Remember, I told you
that I like him for you?

82
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:50,667
If you love him
and you're happy with him,

83
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,633
then I'm happy for you.

84
00:04:55,033 --> 00:04:57,200
I've let go of any expectations,

85
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:59,200
and I accept the fact
that you and Dad

86
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:03,467
will never get back together.

87
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:06,767
Remember, I've been longing to
have a connection with my dad.

88
00:05:09,067 --> 00:05:13,500
It came true because
you let me talk to him.

89
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:16,200
So, thank you.

90
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,367
I love you, Mom.

91
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,433
I love you too, sweetie.

92
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,567
It's good, isn't it?

93
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,933
One more episode?

94
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,000
Maybe next time, sweetie.

95
00:05:36,167 --> 00:05:41,067
If it's okay, I want to watch
Coleen's video again.

96
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,500
Sure, Dad, wait a minute.

97
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:48,133
Here you go.

98
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:17,067
- Hazel.
- Mom.

99
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:20,967
Mom, give my phone back.

100
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,833
<i>- How are you?
- What is this?</i>

101
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:24,600
- What?
- I'm Coleen,

102
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:26,167
your youngest daughter.

103
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:27,900
Don't tell me this is your
daughter, too, Manuel.

104
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:30,567
<i> Dad, you know what...</i>

105
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:31,367
Mom, give my phone back.

106
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,300
Answer my question.

107
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:36,333
<i>- But if I tell you...
- Who is this?</i>

108
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:39,767
Why are you watching her video?

109
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,400
That's Coleen.

110
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:43,367
She's my youngest daughter
with Felma.

111
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,000
So what's going to happen now?

112
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:56,167
Do you think Mom and Uncle Noah
will reconcile?

113
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,367
Should we do something?

114
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,033
I understood Uncle Noah's
sentiment when I talked to him.

115
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:07,633
Mom is the only one who could
fix things between them.

116
00:07:07,767 --> 00:07:09,000
Think about it.

117
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:12,167
If Mom is still in love
with her ex-husband,

118
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,667
no matter what Uncle Noah does,
it won't work.

119
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:15,600
He'll still lose.

120
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,633
Hey.

121
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,500
Why are you acting like that?
I didn't do anything.

122
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:31,900
What? We're just talking
about work.

123
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:33,133
It's work-related stuff.

124
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:35,200
That's right,
and it's getting late.

125
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:35,867
You should go to sleep.

126
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,833
Go to your room.

127
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:39,900
You have an early
start tomorrow.

128
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:42,400
Don't you have an early
start tomorrow, too?

129
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:45,067
Especially you, you have
to drop Tetay off at school.

130
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,300
Okay, fine.

131
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:52,300
Since you're not going anywhere.

132
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:58,833
We're talking about important
family matter.

133
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:02,167
But I doubt that you can
help us out

134
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:05,833
because it's obvious
who you're siding with.

135
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:07,233
You're smart, right?

136
00:08:07,367 --> 00:08:08,567
So you must understand
what we're talking about.

137
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:11,333
Because this kind of
conversation is only for allies.

138
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:17,767
I think I get it.

139
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,700
Well...

140
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,533
It's about mom, right?

141
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:27,867
What makes you think that
I'm not on your side?

142
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,067
I'm team Noah!

143
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:31,633
What are you talking about?

144
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:32,533
I know you're siding
with that loser!

145
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:38,667
You know what, that's the
only thing that makes me upset.

146
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:43,100
Whenever you call Dad
all kinds of names.

147
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:47,033
I accept the fact that you don't
see him as your dad.

148
00:08:47,167 --> 00:08:48,833
I understand that.

149
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:51,967
I'm not going to go
against you on that part.

150
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,567
So, you're not pushing mom
to get back together

151
00:08:54,733 --> 00:08:55,700
with your dad?

152
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,033
He's our dad.

153
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:04,033
And I had a talk
with mom earlier.

154
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:08,633
I told her that
I like Uncle Noah.

155
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:12,067
I told her if she loves
him and wants to marry him,

156
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:15,100
she has my full support.

157
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:17,667
And I can see how much
Uncle Noah loves her.

158
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:21,733
You're not trying to play us?

159
00:09:21,867 --> 00:09:22,867
Aren't you a prankster?

160
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,867
I'm not!

161
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,967
You don't want to believe me?

162
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:27,900
Fine!

163
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,067
You and Daisy won't
end up together.

164
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,733
Why are you bringing her up?

165
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:33,100
Don't try to get Daisy
involved in this.

166
00:09:33,233 --> 00:09:34,467
We're taking things
to the next level.

167
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,033
What?

168
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:36,900
You don't believe me?

169
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,000
We're almost there.

170
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:40,633
So here's the plan.

171
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:44,867
So, clearly,
we are all Team Noah.

172
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:50,633
Now, we need to do something
to get them back together.

173
00:09:50,767 --> 00:09:51,900
So the wedding
won't be called off.

174
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:52,867
Game.

175
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,700
-Let's go.
-Coleen, you're sure about this?

176
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,167
I am.

177
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:59,100
I just have to make
sure you understand.

178
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:00,900
I'm telling you...

179
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:03,500
That's why you're still single.

180
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:05,000
Do I look like
I want a boyfriend?

181
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,333
If you want a relationship,
I'm fine.

182
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,000
Is this your idea?

183
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:17,267
Didn't I tell you not to
communicate with them anymore?

184
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,333
Why are you so stubborn?

185
00:10:20,467 --> 00:10:22,433
Why do you have the courage
to disobey me?

186
00:10:22,567 --> 00:10:24,800
I just want to make Dad happy.

187
00:10:24,933 --> 00:10:26,867
Hazel, you can get mad at me.

188
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,067
Leave Jessica out of this.

189
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,100
You want to make him happy?

190
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:31,933
Even if it means you
have to betray me!

191
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,100
You're so ungrateful.

192
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,067
Hazel!

193
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,400
Hazel, don't hurt her!

194
00:10:35,567 --> 00:10:36,600
- What now?
- Hazel!

195
00:10:36,733 --> 00:10:37,967
- You want me to hurt you?
- Hazel, that's enough!

196
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:38,900
I need to!

197
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,233
- Hazel!
- I need to teach you a lesson!

198
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:42,567
- Hazel, don't hurt the child!
- You dare to do this?

199
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:44,200
- Hazel!
- Are you fighting me?

200
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,133
Listen to me!

201
00:10:45,267 --> 00:10:46,233
Do you know what...

202
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:47,100
Hazel, wait!

203
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:48,533
their mother did to me?

204
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:49,800
Hazel!

205
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:52,433
Hazel! I said, stop it!

206
00:10:52,567 --> 00:10:54,000
- Hazel!
- You should be siding with me!

207
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:55,500
- Stay out of this!
- Hazel, stop!

208
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:56,700
Mom, stop!

209
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:58,767
- I'm hurting.
- I don't care!

210
00:10:58,900 --> 00:10:59,900
Hazel, that's enough!

211
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:02,200
You really have to get hurt
before you learn!

212
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:05,767
Hazel, you're hurting her!

213
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:06,600
What am I to you?

214
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:08,900
Hazel!

215
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:10,533
Why are you siding with them?

216
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:12,800
Who am I to you?

217
00:11:12,933 --> 00:11:15,467
Hazel!
Have pity on her!

218
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,167
Don't touch me!

219
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,700
Stay out of this!

220
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,467
- Calm down!
- Stay out of this!

221
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,633
Don't touch me!

222
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:23,567
I'm not done with you!

223
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,767
You hear me?

224
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,233
- I'm not done with you yet!
- Calm down! Calm down!

225
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:27,300
No!

226
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:38,133
Sweetie, why is your classmate
taking so long?

227
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:42,067
Your siblings might
be home by now.

228
00:11:42,233 --> 00:11:44,867
Why didn't you just ask her to
bring your project to our house?

229
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,867
Or we could have picked
it up at her house.

230
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,700
Wait, Mom.

231
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,167
Rona says she's getting close.

232
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:55,100
She's here!

233
00:11:55,233 --> 00:11:55,867
Hey.

234
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:32,067
Dad...

235
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,233
Mom is scaring me.

236
00:12:34,367 --> 00:12:36,000
I think she'll hurt me even more

237
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:38,500
if it's just the two of us at
home.

238
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,233
I'm sorry.

239
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:44,800
I didn't get to protect you
because of my condition.

240
00:12:45,867 --> 00:12:49,000
And I'm sorry that
your mom hurt me because of me.

241
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,700
Dad,

242
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,300
I just really want
you to be happy.

243
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:58,533
I saw how genuinely happy
you were

244
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:01,067
when one of your children
with Miss Felma

245
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:06,300
acknowledged you
and talked to you.

246
00:13:08,767 --> 00:13:09,800
You know what,

247
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:12,900
she was just a little baby
when I left.

248
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:17,200
She didn't have
any memories of me.

249
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,867
But compared to her brother
and sister,

250
00:13:21,267 --> 00:13:24,467
she's the one who longs
to see and know me.

251
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:29,633
And I truly felt
Coleen's sincerity, Dad.

252
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:31,400
She truly loves you.

253
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:35,967
I'm hoping that...

254
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,433
I will get to hug her one day.

255
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,233
I'm always praying that...

256
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:46,600
that she could be the reason

257
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:49,233
for Jeffrey and Andrea's hearts
to soften.

258
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:51,733
And finally, forgive me.

259
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:59,833
I still think those goals
are totally doable, Dad.

260
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:14,267
I'm sorry if we have to do this.

261
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,567
You guys need to talk
to each other.

262
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,433
You should face each other...

263
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:21,967
and talk about your issues.

264
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:29,933
We want you guys to patch things
up before we leave this place.

265
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:33,233
Mom, I want you to know
where I stand.

266
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:36,400
I'm team Noah, too.

267
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:37,833
No,

268
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:39,500
I don't want your mom
to feel pressured.

269
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,133
I don't want her
to make a decision

270
00:14:42,267 --> 00:14:43,767
just because she feels forced

271
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,600
or because she's afraid of
hurting someone else's feelings.

272
00:14:48,633 --> 00:14:50,100
If she needs space,

273
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:51,400
that's what we'll give her.

274
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:00,100
Just a curious question, dad.

275
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,333
If you hadn't been shot,

276
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,800
what could have been
your long-term plan?

277
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,800
Would you have stuck
with the separation from mom?

278
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:13,667
Yes, sweetie.

279
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,000
I'm sorry, but...

280
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:19,500
I have decided
to leave your mom.

281
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:26,233
I was planning to save up money
so I could get custody of you.

282
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:28,967
And then,

283
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,433
I will do everything

284
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:32,900
to get Felma
and my children's forgiveness.

285
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:34,233
You know what, if that happens,

286
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:38,367
I would be the happiest person
in the world.

287
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,900
And I still think those goals
are totally doable, Dad.

288
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:46,633
Dad, you deserve to be happy,

289
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:48,667
and I'll help you achieve
that happiness.

290
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:51,700
Who knows? You could still
restore your relationship

291
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:53,033
with your original family.

292
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:57,633
I know that you all want me
to be happy.

293
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,700
I appreciate all the efforts
you're making...

294
00:16:01,967 --> 00:16:04,000
and making me feel.

295
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:06,133
And believe me,

296
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:07,667
I'm weighing everything in.

297
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:12,800
I'm thinking about
all your opinions.

298
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,233
But in the end,

299
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:18,133
I am the one who gets to decide

300
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:21,367
what will truly make me happy.

301
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:24,533
These past few days,

302
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,100
I've come to realize

303
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,000
that sometimes...

304
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:34,300
it's hard to tell
the difference between...

305
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:36,400
love...

306
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:37,567
and pity.

307
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:40,533
You thought...

308
00:16:41,733 --> 00:16:44,433
you loved the person,
but it turns out...

309
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,033
you just feel sorry for them.

310
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:48,867
And I don't want to be unfair.

311
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,033
I want...

312
00:16:52,167 --> 00:16:55,167
love to matter more...

313
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:56,600
than pity.

314
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,033
Noah...

315
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:03,067
before this day,

316
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:05,067
before the kids
brought us together,

317
00:17:07,733 --> 00:17:09,100
I had already prayed for this

318
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:12,333
and thought long and hard
about my decision.

319
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,733
Noah maybe it's better if...

320
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:21,133
we don't go through
with the wedding.

321
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:39,500
Dad, I promise I'll find a way.

322
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:40,967
I will do whatever it takes

323
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,267
to bring you back
to the Philippines.

324
00:17:50,533 --> 00:17:52,800
You're calling off the wedding?

325
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:54,033
Mom, are you serious about this?

326
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:57,800
No, Felma.

327
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:00,467
You're not calling off
the wedding.

328
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:02,700
Let's just postpone it.

329
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:05,733
I will wait
whenever you're ready.

330
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:10,200
I will never be ready, Noah.

331
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,867
I don't want
to be unfair to you.

332
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:16,867
I am the problem.

333
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:20,300
I'm not ready to be tied down
in a relationship.

334
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,633
I'm sorry.

335
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:28,533
If I can call off the wedding,

336
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,267
it only means that...

337
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:35,100
you're not the priority
in my life.

338
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,600
Who is it then?

339
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,700
Your ex-husband?

340
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,700
Do you still love him?

341
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:45,133
That's not true, Andrea.

342
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:48,667
I pity him,

343
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:51,800
but that doesn't mean
that I love him.

344
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:54,033
He has nothing to do
with my decision.

345
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,467
I'm sorry.

346
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:04,333
I'm sorry.

347
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,400
I still have a lot of baggage.

348
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,133
Ever since we were abandoned,

349
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,233
I couldn't bring myself
to commit.

350
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:17,300
I can't.

351
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,800
I will never be able to.

352
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:27,200
I can't handle a relationship.

353
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,633
For eighteen years...

354
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,500
I have lived alone.

355
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:36,433
All I thought about
was my children.

356
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:38,267
They are my priority.

357
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,300
And that will never change.

358
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,667
I'm sorry.

359
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,300
I love you,

360
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:54,100
but my love for you
is not enough...

361
00:19:54,233 --> 00:19:56,167
for me to give up...

362
00:19:59,767 --> 00:20:01,933
a lifetime commitment.

363
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:05,300
You deserve to be happy.

364
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:08,933
But with someone else.

365
00:20:09,067 --> 00:20:10,200
It's not me.

366
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:14,467
I'm not the one for you, Noah.

367
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,567
I'm sorry.

368
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:17,767
I'm sorry.

369
00:20:37,567 --> 00:20:38,800
Felma.

370
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:40,267
Felma, wait.

371
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,800
Felma, let's talk.

372
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:43,800
Felma,

373
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:44,967
what's the matter with you?

374
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:48,500
I never had doubts about us.

375
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:53,033
But you,
you were full of doubts.

376
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:56,200
I never had a doubt about you,

377
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,267
but I doubt myself.

378
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:03,000
I can't commit
to this relationship.

379
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:05,233
I can't do it.

380
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:06,500
It's better this way,

381
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:08,167
that I realized it sooner.

382
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,367
Not when we're already married,

383
00:21:09,533 --> 00:21:11,800
and then I realized that
I can't give you everything.

384
00:21:13,067 --> 00:21:14,833
Felma...

385
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,367
I'm not asking for anything.

386
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:19,567
Your love is enough.

387
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:21,900
Darn it, Felma.

388
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,667
I waited for you.

389
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,067
I never gave up on you.

390
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:28,133
And now...

391
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:31,233
you're dropping me
just like that?

392
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:33,933
Felma,

393
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:37,267
is that how worthless
I am to you?

394
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,567
You're important to me.

395
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:42,967
I can see your worth.

396
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,367
But...

397
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:47,533
not in the way
you wanted me to see it.

398
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:52,000
I want to believe your decision
has nothing to do with Manuel.

399
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:54,367
Felma...

400
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:57,833
are you telling the truth?

401
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:01,833
He has nothing to do with this.

402
00:22:02,767 --> 00:22:04,167
You have to believe me.

403
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:07,267
Then why did you change
your mind?

404
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:09,733
Because of the space
you gave me.

405
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:12,933
That's when I realized...

406
00:22:13,067 --> 00:22:15,567
that I'm content with my life,

407
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:18,100
that I'm not thinking
of anyone else.

408
00:22:20,733 --> 00:22:22,133
I am used to being alone.

409
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,200
Just myself.

410
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:25,633
I make decisions for myself.

411
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:28,633
What do you mean?

412
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:31,267
When Manuel called me.

413
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:33,600
<i> I'm not going to answer that.</i>

414
00:22:33,733 --> 00:22:34,600
<i> Answer it.</i>

415
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:35,500
<i>I said,
I'm not going to answer it.</i>

416
00:22:35,633 --> 00:22:37,233
<i> I promised you.</i>

417
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:38,700
<i>- He'll get tired eventually.
- Answer it.</i>

418
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:39,933
<i> He'll stop calling.</i>

419
00:22:41,233 --> 00:22:42,767
No,

420
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:45,533
you made the decision

421
00:22:45,667 --> 00:22:47,533
whether I should answer
the call or not.

422
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,233
Actually,

423
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:51,600
you took the call

424
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:54,267
after I told you not to.

425
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,800
You made the decision for me.

426
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:59,033
<i> Stop involving Felma,</i>

427
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:01,733
<i>stop involving us
and the kids with your problem.</i>

428
00:23:01,867 --> 00:23:03,233
<i> So please, Manuel.</i>

429
00:23:04,367 --> 00:23:05,733
<i> Leave us alone.</i>

430
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:08,400
That's one of my realizations.

431
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:14,800
I don't want anyone else
to decide for me.

432
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,267
The kids...

433
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:21,633
they set us up, they set me up.

434
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,833
I understand how they feel.

435
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:26,167
They want us to be together.

436
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:29,367
But it's the same thing.

437
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:31,733
They want to decide for me.

438
00:23:33,233 --> 00:23:36,200
I don't like it if I'm being
told what to do.

439
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:38,600
I want to decide for myself.

440
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:41,533
I don't want to be manipulated.

441
00:23:41,667 --> 00:23:43,600
What I want is...

442
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:48,000
to have full control
over my decisions,

443
00:23:48,133 --> 00:23:49,667
over my life.

444
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:55,300
I'm sorry, Noah, if I hurt you.

445
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:20,767
I'm going to get going, Dad.
I'll be back, maybe on Thursday.

446
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:22,100
- I'll see you then.
- Be safe.

447
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:26,767
What are you doing here?

448
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:30,700
You're supposed to be at school.

449
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:33,433
I told you last night, Mommy.
It's exam week.

450
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:35,733
I was exempted
from my last subject today.

451
00:24:35,867 --> 00:24:38,000
That's why I got out
of school early.

452
00:24:40,267 --> 00:24:41,333
Well,

453
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:43,033
I didn't hear you.

454
00:24:43,167 --> 00:24:45,000
Because I was busy, remember?

455
00:24:45,133 --> 00:24:47,300
I was looking for a job online.

456
00:24:47,433 --> 00:24:49,067
Because I got fired from my job.

457
00:24:50,233 --> 00:24:53,000
Mom, can Dad and I
have our phones back now?

458
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,433
No.

459
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:56,267
But that's our phone.

460
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:59,000
Mom, I respect you,
but respect works both ways.

461
00:24:59,133 --> 00:25:01,933
You need to respect us, too,
especially Dad.

462
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:03,833
You don't have the right to just
take our stuff like that.

463
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,100
Shut up!

464
00:25:07,533 --> 00:25:08,833
What are you talking about?

465
00:25:09,867 --> 00:25:11,100
You want to get your phone back

466
00:25:11,233 --> 00:25:13,200
so you can contact his family
back in the Philippines.

467
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:14,967
Just his youngest daughter, Mom.

468
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,900
She was just a baby
the last time he saw her.

469
00:25:17,033 --> 00:25:19,700
He's not cheating if that's what
you're worried about.

470
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,433
So, can you please allow it?

471
00:25:21,567 --> 00:25:22,833
I don't care!

472
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:25,133
Jessica,

473
00:25:25,267 --> 00:25:26,867
I'm your mother.

474
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,533
You should be loyal to me.

475
00:25:28,667 --> 00:25:30,467
You know what,
I was having a hard time

476
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:33,567
because of your dad, and you're
still taking his side?

477
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,167
Mom, he's lonely.

478
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:36,467
He just wants to feel

479
00:25:36,633 --> 00:25:39,433
like someone still loves and
cares for him, apart from me.

480
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:41,900
Maybe he can find that
in my half-sister as well

481
00:25:42,033 --> 00:25:44,100
because he clearly
isn't getting it from you.

482
00:25:44,233 --> 00:25:45,267
How dare you? How dare you!

483
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,867
- Hazel!
- You're a fool!

484
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:49,933
Hazel, stop it! Don't hurt her!

485
00:26:00,533 --> 00:26:02,833
I'm not taking back
anything I said.

486
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:04,267
That's my decision.

487
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,033
I'm not a teenager anymore!

488
00:26:06,167 --> 00:26:08,233
Why do you feel the need
to set me up with my boyfriend

489
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,500
just to get us back together?

490
00:26:09,633 --> 00:26:11,467
He's always been the one
by my side.

491
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:14,367
Even after you took away
his right to work.

492
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,867
I got to grow up with him!

493
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,800
I grew up full of love and care.

494
00:26:19,933 --> 00:26:21,167
He never laid a hand on me,

495
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:24,200
so don't wonder why
my loyalty lies with him!

496
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:26,867
- You ungrateful child!
- Hazel!

497
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,233
- Hazel, that's enough!
- She needs to learn her lesson!

498
00:26:29,367 --> 00:26:33,667
You told Uncle Noah that you're
not ready to commit?

499
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:36,433
What if Dad wants to get
back together with you?
